'''''The Lundi Series''''' were recorded lectures of [[Professor/Legends|Professor]] [[Murk Lundi]] used by the [[New Jedi Order]] for insight into the history of the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]].

==History==
''The Lundi Series'' were initially met with skepticism by [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Jedi historian|historians]], as Professor Lundi failed to cite specific sources, and some data appeared to be his own inventions to improve his academic reputation. Lundi was considered a better teacher than researcher. Many of the findings in the ''Series'' were ultimately corroborated by the [[Wavlud Manuscript]], another document on Sith history.<ref name="TEGTTF-p3">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref>

